how to Download Tor for Linux

1. Download Tor Browser 
https://www.torproject.org/

2. Extract files and cut folder to Desktop

3. Open Terminal
chown -R root:root (name-of-Tor-folder)

4. Open folder
ls
cd tor-browser
cd Browser

open start-tor-browser in leafpad

search for root in file

add #
#
#
#


#if [ "`id -u`" -eq 0 ]; then
#	complain "The Tor Browser Bundle should not be run as root.  Exiting."
#	exit 1
#fi

save and close the file

5. move Tor-browser folder to etc folder

6. apt install alacarte

7. Now Open Main Menu

go under application Menu

Lets add Tor-Browser to Application menu
Click new Item
Browse
find the Tor folder etc/ and open the Browser folder in their you will find start-tor-browser choose that.

now click on icon and go to etc/ tor folder open browser folder and click chrome/icon

8. now name the file and save to Main Menu .
9. It is now under Application Menu.

Enjoy

But remember Tor does NOT make you 100% / :-)

